# CameraControlSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Detects camera input each frame and drives the gameplay camera. Returns early until both
InputStateSingletonComponent and at least one OrthographicCameraComponent exist. Reads held WASD keys
(pan) and the mouse scroll offset (zoom); when there is any camera input it reads the camera's current
zoom level and the camera entity's PositionComponent, computes the new clamped zoom and the new world
position (pan speed scales with zoom, scaled by the frame delta), and emits a
SetCameraRequestOneFrameComponent for the engine CameraSystem to apply. No-ops on a frame with no
camera input.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read | Held WASD keys; guard (returns early if absent) |
| MouseScrolledEventComponent | read | Per-frame scroll offset that drives zoom |
| OrthographicCameraComponent | read | Current zoom level; locates the camera entity; guard (returns early if no camera) |
| PositionComponent | read | The camera's current world position (pan origin) |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SetCameraRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | New zoom + world position; emitted only on a frame with camera input |
